## The problem most business owners do not talk about

You are good at your trade. That is not the issue. The issue is everything that happens around the trade — the calls you miss when you are on a job, the follow-ups you forget, the quotes that go cold because you ran out of time.

These are not failures of effort. They are failures of system.

## What automation actually means

Automation does not mean robots replacing people. It means the routine, repetitive tasks — sending a reminder, following up a missed call, asking for a review — happen without you having to think about them.

You set them up once. They run every day without you.

## Three automations every UK trade business should have first

**Missed call text-back.** When you miss a call while on a job, the system sends a text within 30 seconds. "Sorry I missed your call — how can I help?" That lead is not lost to your competitor.

**Appointment reminders.** The system texts your clients 24 hours before and 2 hours before their appointment. No-shows drop by up to 60 percent.

**Review requests.** 24 hours after a job is complete, a text goes out asking for a Google review. Your rating grows on autopilot without you having to ask face to face.

